activities.name: History and Physical Examination
activities.description: A standard physical examination will be performed at screening. Record age, gender, presence of diabetes and its type and duration, diabetic treatment, prior foot ulcers, prior amputations or foot surgeries, co-existing medical conditions. Use Kaplan Co-morbidity Index to score disease severity.

activities.name: Informed Consent
activities.description: Obtain written informed consent from participant prior to any study related procedures

activities.name: Medical History
activities.description: Record socio-demographics (age, gender, BMI, education, marital status) and medical history (health status including comorbidities, history of falls, history of hospitalization, prior surgery, duration of diagnosed MCI, co-existing medical conditions, hearing and visual performance, frailty status), medication use

activities.name: Socio-demographics
activities.description: Record age, gender, BMI, education, marital status and other demographic information

activities.name: Social Factors
activities.description: Evaluate marital status, years of education, type of work, tobacco history (pack years, current smoker, current use of chewing tobacco, previous smoker, no tobacco history)

activities.name: Quality of Life (Promise Global)
activities.description: Health related questionnaire for quality of life assessment

activities.name: Demographics
activities.description: Demographics questionnaire

activities.name: Beck Anxiety Scale
activities.description: Anxiety assessment questionnaire

activities.name: Pain-Mobility
activities.description: Pain and mobility assessment questionnaire

activities.name: Fear of Falling (FES-I)
activities.description: Falls Efficacy Scale - International for fear of falling assessment

activities.name: Frailty (Fried Frailty)
activities.description: Fried Frailty criteria assessment (Weight loss >10 pounds in preceding year; Grip strength; Low levels of physical activity; 15 foot walk time; Exhaustion)

activities.name: MOCA for cognitive status
activities.description: Montreal Cognitive Assessment for cognitive status evaluation

activities.name: Depression (CES-D)
activities.description: Center for Epidemiologic Studies Depression Scale

activities.name: Trail-making task A and B
activities.description: Trail-Making Test A and B for cognitive assessment

activities.name: LifeSpace
activities.description: LifeSpace questionnaire for mobility assessment

activities.name: ePro Lawton and Katz Scale
activities.description: Electronic patient reported outcome for daily activities assessment using Lawton and Katz Scale

activities.name: Acceptability questionnaire
activities.description: Questionnaire to assess acceptability of the intervention at follow up visit

activities.name: Peripheral Neuropathy (VPT testing)
activities.description: Vibration Perception Threshold (VPT) testing, evaluated at the distal great toe, heel and 5th metatarsal

activities.name: Standard foot questionnaire
activities.description: Standard foot questionnaire to assess any potential limitation which may influence the ability of participants to perform iTMT using ankle-foot trail making

activities.name: Frailty status (Fried Frailty criteria)
activities.description: Examine frailty status using Fried Frailty criteria

activities.name: Height and weight measurement
activities.description: Measure height and weight to determine body mass index

activities.name: Gait assessment (LegSys sensors)
activities.description: Gait performance assessed using validated body worn sensors (LegSys, Biosensics LLC). Device uses five sensor modules attached to right and left anterior shins, right and left anterior thighs, and posteriorly to the lower back. Parameters estimated: velocity, stride length, stride time, double support, single support, stride-to-stride variability, and gait initiation. Gait assessed over 20 meters at habitual and maximum speed.

activities.name: Balance assessment (BalanSens sensors)
activities.description: Balance quantified using validated body worn sensors (BalanSens, Biosensics LLC). System measures ankle and hip motion in 3D, 2D COM sway and RCI in ML and AP directions. Balance assessed according to Romberg protocol during eyes-open and eyes-closed condition during double, semi-tandem, and full tandem stances.

activities.name: Timed-up-and-go (TUG)
activities.description: Subject stands up from a chair, walks 3 meters, walks back to the chair, and sits down as fast and safely as possible

activities.name: Upper Extremity Test (arm motion)
activities.description: Measure arm motion using validated wearable sensor system (LegSys). One sensor placed on wrist to capture arm motion. Subject flexes and extends arm for 20 seconds at fast speed, then repeats while counting backwards (dual task).

activities.name: PAMSys wearable device (48 hours)
activities.description: Wearable device (PAMSys) measuring number of steps taken, duration of sitting, standing, walking and lying, time taken and number of transitions from sit to stand, and walking speed for 48 hours. Device attached to pendant worn around neck.

activities.name: Exergaming platform exercise program
activities.description: Exercise program using Exergaming platform, twice per week for approximately 30 minutes. Includes ankle reaching tasks in upward-downward direction and side-ward reaching task, progressing to diagonal directions and motor-cognitive tasks.

activities.name: Motor-Cognitive Exercise program (TMT)
activities.description: Motor-cognitive exercise including working memory inspired from paper-pencil Trail-Making test (TMT). Includes three levels of motor-cognitive complexities: Fixed-order TMT, Random-order TMT, and Number-Letter-order TMT.

activities.name: Phone calls (3 and 6 months post follow-up)
activities.description: Contact subjects at three and six months after follow up visit to ask about accidental falls and other health questions

activities.name: Photos and media collection
activities.description: Take photos, film videos and/or record audio during visits to monitor progress. May be used for scientific publications/oral presentations with face covered per journal policy.

notes.text: Phase I: 15 subjects with mild dementia and cognitive impairments in single arm 6 weeks remote exercise intervention
Phase II: 100 subjects randomized to intervention or control group for 12 weeks exercise program
Inclusion: MoCA score 20-26, ambulatory (able to walk 20m), living independently with caregiver
Exclusion: Immobility, severe cognitive impairment (MoCA < 20), stroke, Parkinson disease, psychiatric conditions
Participants compensated $50 per baseline/follow-up visit and $10 per exercise session
